alwaysApply: true
---
After completing ANY module or meaningful change you MUST, in the same change:
1. Update PROJECT_STATE.json: set the module's status, last_touched (ISO-8601 UTC),
   test_coverage, and notes. Add an ADR entry if a design decision was made.
2. Append a dated entry to the "## Build Log" section at the bottom of README.md,
   newest first, format: "### YYYY-MM-DD � <module>: <one-line summary>".
3. Never edit the two contracts in contracts/ without bumping canonical_schema_version
   and recording an ADR.
Do not mark a module "tested" unless tests exist and pass.
